Urbex = urban exploration. Furbex = urban exploration with a furry twist 🐶. Alice, a photographer and urban explorer, uses #GoogleEarth and #StreetView to find abandoned buildings around Europe, where she takes photos of her dog Claire. See today’s story to learn more about what @alicevankempen calls Furbex—and to see more of Claire’s adventures. #SearchOn

24-year-old Daniel DeLeon never thought he would become an engineer–but a lifelong passion for music sent him down an unexpected path. Using TensorFlow, Google’s open-source machine learning tool, he tracks whale calls to better understand endangered marine life. See more of Daniel’s journey in our story today. #SearchOn

#GrowWithGoogle Stories, Vol 5: “We’re not your traditional pharmacy,” says President Anthony Qaiyum of @merzapothecary, located in Chicago. The “143-year-old startup,” as he likes to call it, has always been quick to embrace the power of technology. 85 percent of the business’s marketing budget is now dedicated to digital. They use Google’s advertising program to reach customers who are searching for their specialty products. “AdWords is the magical vehicle that gets you in front of the people who really need what you’re selling.” #SmallBusinessWeek
#teampixel photographer @worldthroughashutter captured a beautiful combination of sandstone, marble, birds and blue skies at Safdarjung's Tomb in New Delhi.

#GrowWithGoogle Stories, Vol 4: “I was sketching dresses for fun and discovered a real love for designing clothing,” recalls Lauren Stokes, “I didn’t want to give up on this passion.” In 2013, Lauren left her job and founded @laurenjames, a combination of her and her son’s names. Offering classically-inspired clothing with a modern flair, the business has grown from a small family shop to one of the fastest growing companies in Arkansas. Today they’re attracting fashionable customers from across North America and Europe with fun and instructional YouTube videos to showcase their new seasonal lines. “We do videos for all of our launches and sneak peeks.” #SmallBusinessWeek

Now premiering on our homepage: The first-ever VR and 360° video #GoogleDoodle starring illusionist and film director Georges Méliès, whose films transported viewers into magical worlds and zany stories. Shown here in behind-the-scenes sketches, today's Doodle highlights some of the iconic techniques and styles found in Méliès’ films, including strong colors, engaging storylines and optical effects. #BacktotheMoon

#GrowWithGoogle Stories, Vol 3: “We started this company when we were sophomores in college. So it was not something I really planned on doing as my career,” explains Eric Delgado, co-founder of @ropelacesupply, a company he founded with Victoria Weiss that offers sneaker fanatics a way to customize their shoes with different colored laces. “I have a better grasp on what sneaker heads would like because I buy new shoes all the time.” With a little help from Google, his theory that he’s the man for his audience was confirmed. “Google Analytics helps us learn a good amount about our customer base, which in turn helps us identify new opportunities and informs the kinds of shoelaces we design.” #SmallBusinessWeek

#GrowWithGoogle Stories, Vol 2: "It's super niche and not glamorous and that's why we like it,” says Will McDonald, co-founder and CEO of #RugPadUSA, who manufactures padding used to keep area rugs in place. Will worked in finance for his first two years out of college before pivoting and starting his own business at age 23. He’s come a long way since then, reviving massive warehouses in Bridgeport and Ansonia, Connecticut and enlisting a 100% local workforce. Now he’s focused on spreading the word. “Google has a huge impact on us. We're typically the number one search result when you type in ‘rug pads.’ So we depend on Google for a significant amount of our business.” #SmallBusinessWeek

#GrowWithGoogle Stories, Vol 1: “It's a fun, old fashioned type of general store and we sell over a 100 different flavors of soda pop bottles, candy, gifts, apparel, a variety of goods,” says Alicia Rehmert, President of @langegeneralstore. The rustic authenticity of this early 20th century staple reminds customers of a simpler time. But the nostalgia is powered by technology of the here-and-now. Over the past year, Lange General Store has more than doubled their sales and number of customers. “We plan to double again, and then again,” Alicia shares. “Google has helped us grow our e-commerce business, and we've only tapped the surface.” #SmallBusinessWeek

To celebrate the art of Chinese calligraphy, Singaporean artist Malik Mazlan, in collaboration with Hiverlab, is introducing the craft to younger generations with the help of Google #TiltBrush–a tool that lets you paint in 3D space with virtual reality. Check out today’s story to see how Malik is bringing this ancient art form to life in VR.

A happy (and earthy) 1st birthday to the new #GoogleEarth! 🎉 Since we launched a fresh new version one year ago, millions of people searched to the edge of the world and beyond. Here's to many more spins around the sun!

Twinkle, twinkle, little #Doogler… 🌟 It’s #NationalPetDay, and today we’re celebrating Twinkle, a senior pup from our San Francisco office. Adopted late last year, this little lady loves playtime and all the dog treats she can get her paws on.

Illegal loggers and deforestation threaten the survival of the Amazon rainforest and the indigenous people who live there. But the Tembé tribe in central Amazon and nonprofit @rainforestcx are fighting back with an ambitious plan involving recycled cell phones and TensorFlow, our open-source machine learning tool. Learn more on our story today. #SearchOn
